  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project Rhino K9 Unit: Defending African Wildlife</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The greatest threat today to two of South Africa&apos;s most iconic species - the Black and White Rhino - come in the form of furtive raids by poachers armed with high-calibre rifles, night-vision equipment, getaway vehicles and backed by a vast, well-funded international criminal network. With their superior sense of smell, hearing and unique physical capabilities, well trained canines are a valuable supplement to law enforcement and a critical tool in combatting this war against rhino poaching.</narrative>
  </description>
